</div><!--$--><div class="pt-6 pb-6 sm:pt-14 sm:py-10 sm:w-full"><h2 class=" faq-title text-s-24 pb-7 m-0 sm:pb-3 sm:text-s-20 sm:leading-7 sm:font-bold">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="vertical vertical-stack accordion has-content border-t-sm border-grey-300 border-opacity-50 sm:border-opacity-100 pr-8 text-s-20 sm:border-b-sm sm:border-x-0 sm:rounded-none sm:px-2 sm:mt-0 border-t-0 "><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-header accordion-header-collapsed py-5 text-s-20 sm:my-auto sm:text-s-20 sm:font-medium sm:py-6"><div class="accordion-header-content font-semibold sm:text-s-14 sm:leading-6 sm:font-semibold">Do all public institutions in Maharashtra observe these holidays uniformly?</div><button class="button button-default rounded-sm accordion-icon undefined bg-transparent" type="button"><svg width="10" class="rotate-180 " height="6" viewBox="0 0 10 6" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0.83712 5.5028C1.16307 5.82646 1.68939 5.82553 2.0142 5.50072L5.24336 2.27156L8.48054 5.50169C8.80529 5.82573 9.33115 5.82544 9.65554 5.50104C9.98019 5.1764 9.98019 4.65005 9.65554 4.3254L5.83262 0.502481C5.50718 0.177044 4.97954 0.177044 4.65411 0.502481L0.835034 4.32155C0.508602 4.64799 0.509537 5.17752 0.83712 5.5028Z" fill="#314259"></path></svg></button></div><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-detail-panel hidden partnerFAQ overflow-x-hidden text-base pb-5 sm:py-5 sm:pt-0 mt-[-18px]"><div><p><meta></p><p><span style="background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Yes, state government offices, schools, and colleges adhere strictly to this list. Banks and cooperatives follow suit, with the April 1 annual closing dedicated to financial year-end activities.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="vertical vertical-stack accordion has-content border-t-sm border-grey-300 border-opacity-50 sm:border-opacity-100 pr-8 text-s-20 sm:border-b-sm sm:border-x-0 sm:rounded-none sm:px-2 sm:mt-0 border-t-0 "><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-header accordion-header-collapsed py-5 text-s-20 sm:my-auto sm:text-s-20 sm:font-medium sm:py-6"><div class="accordion-header-content font-semibold sm:text-s-14 sm:leading-6 sm:font-semibold">Is Gudi Padwa a public holiday in Maharashtra for 2026?</div><button class="button button-default rounded-sm accordion-icon undefined bg-transparent" type="button"><svg width="10" class="rotate-180 " height="6" viewBox="0 0 10 6" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0.83712 5.5028C1.16307 5.82646 1.68939 5.82553 2.0142 5.50072L5.24336 2.27156L8.48054 5.50169C8.80529 5.82573 9.33115 5.82544 9.65554 5.50104C9.98019 5.1764 9.98019 4.65005 9.65554 4.3254L5.83262 0.502481C5.50718 0.177044 4.97954 0.177044 4.65411 0.502481L0.835034 4.32155C0.508602 4.64799 0.509537 5.17752 0.83712 5.5028Z" fill="#314259"></path></svg></button></div><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-detail-panel hidden partnerFAQ overflow-x-hidden text-base pb-5 sm:py-5 sm:pt-0 mt-[-18px]"><div><p><meta></p><p><span style="background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Yes, Gudi Padwa is a beloved state holiday on Friday, March 20, 2026, kicking off the Marathi New Year with triumphant processions and symbolic bamboo flags.</span></p></div></div></div><div class="vertical vertical-stack accordion has-content border-t-sm border-grey-300 border-opacity-50 sm:border-opacity-100 pr-8 text-s-20 sm:border-b-sm sm:border-x-0 sm:rounded-none sm:px-2 sm:mt-0 border-t-0 "><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-header accordion-header-collapsed py-5 text-s-20 sm:my-auto sm:text-s-20 sm:font-medium sm:py-6"><div class="accordion-header-content font-semibold sm:text-s-14 sm:leading-6 sm:font-semibold">When does Ganesh Chaturthi occur in Maharashtra in 2026?</div><button class="button button-default rounded-sm accordion-icon undefined bg-transparent" type="button"><svg width="10" class="rotate-180 " height="6" viewBox="0 0 10 6" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0.83712 5.5028C1.16307 5.82646 1.68939 5.82553 2.0142 5.50072L5.24336 2.27156L8.48054 5.50169C8.80529 5.82573 9.33115 5.82544 9.65554 5.50104C9.98019 5.1764 9.98019 4.65005 9.65554 4.3254L5.83262 0.502481C5.50718 0.177044 4.97954 0.177044 4.65411 0.502481L0.835034 4.32155C0.508602 4.64799 0.509537 5.17752 0.83712 5.5028Z" fill="#314259"></path></svg></button></div><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-detail-panel hidden partnerFAQ overflow-x-hidden text-base pb-5 sm:py-5 sm:pt-0 mt-[-18px]"><div><p><meta></p><p><span style="background-color:transparent;color:#000000;font-family:Arial,sans-serif;">Ganesh Chaturthi begins on Monday, September 14, 2026, unleashing a 10-day spectacle of devotion, modaks, and colossal idol immersions statewide.</span></p></div></div></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Do all public institutions in Maharashtra observe these holidays uniformly?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, state government offices, schools, and colleges adhere strictly to this list. Banks and cooperatives follow suit, with the April 1 annual closing dedicated to financial year-end activities."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Gudi Padwa a public holiday in Maharashtra for 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, Gudi Padwa is a beloved state holiday on Friday, March 20, 2026, kicking off the Marathi New Year with triumphant processions and symbolic bamboo flags."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When does Ganesh Chaturthi occur in Maharashtra in 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Ganesh Chaturthi begins on Monday, September 14, 2026, unleashing a 10-day spectacle of devotion, modaks, and colossal idol immersions statewide."}}]}</script></div><!--/$--></div></div><div class="px-7 sm:px-5 w-[28%] sm:w-full right-articles-section"><!--$