sm:my-auto sm:text-s-20 sm:font-medium sm:py-6"><div class="accordion-header-content font-semibold sm:text-s-14 sm:leading-6 sm:font-semibold">Is Ugadi a public holiday in Karnataka for 2026?</div><button class="button button-default rounded-sm accordion-icon undefined bg-transparent" type="button"><svg width="10" class="rotate-180 " height="6" viewBox="0 0 10 6" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0.83712 5.5028C1.16307 5.82646 1.68939 5.82553 2.0142 5.50072L5.24336 2.27156L8.48054 5.50169C8.80529 5.82573 9.33115 5.82544 9.65554 5.50104C9.98019 5.1764 9.98019 4.65005 9.65554 4.3254L5.83262 0.502481C5.50718 0.177044 4.97954 0.177044 4.65411 0.502481L0.835034 4.32155C0.508602 4.64799 0.509537 5.17752 0.83712 5.5028Z" fill="#314259"></path></svg></button></div><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-detail-panel hidden partnerFAQ overflow-x-hidden text-base pb-5 sm:py-5 sm:pt-0 mt-[-18px]"><div><p>Yes, Ugadi is a cherished state holiday on Thursday, March 19, 2026, welcoming the New Year with neem-jaggery concoctions and festive prognostications.</p></div></div></div><div class="vertical vertical-stack accordion has-content border-t-sm border-grey-300 border-opacity-50 sm:border-opacity-100 pr-8 text-s-20 sm:border-b-sm sm:border-x-0 sm:rounded-none sm:px-2 sm:mt-0 border-t-0 "><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-header accordion-header-collapsed py-5 text-s-20 sm:my-auto sm:text-s-20 sm:font-medium sm:py-6"><div class="accordion-header-content font-semibold sm:text-s-14 sm:leading-6 sm:font-semibold">When does Deepavali occur in Karnataka in 2026?</div><button class="button button-default rounded-sm accordion-icon undefined bg-transparent" type="button"><svg width="10" class="rotate-180 " height="6" viewBox="0 0 10 6" fill="none" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><path d="M0.83712 5.5028C1.16307 5.82646 1.68939 5.82553 2.0142 5.50072L5.24336 2.27156L8.48054 5.50169C8.80529 5.82573 9.33115 5.82544 9.65554 5.50104C9.98019 5.1764 9.98019 4.65005 9.65554 4.3254L5.83262 0.502481C5.50718 0.177044 4.97954 0.177044 4.65411 0.502481L0.835034 4.32155C0.508602 4.64799 0.509537 5.17752 0.83712 5.5028Z" fill="#314259"></path></svg></button></div><div class="across vertical-stack w-full accordion-detail-panel hidden partnerFAQ overflow-x-hidden text-base pb-5 sm:py-5 sm:pt-0 mt-[-18px]"><div><p>Deepavali is scheduled for Tuesday, November 10, 2026, enveloping the state in a symphony of lights, confections, and tales of divine triumph.</p></div></div></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Are there any tentative holidays in the Karnataka 2026 calendar?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, Islamic festivals including Khutub-E-Ramzan (March 21), Bakrid (May 28), Moharram (June 26), and Eid-e-Milad (August 26) are provisional and could shift slightly depending on lunar sightings.&nbsp;"}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Ugadi a public holiday in Karnataka for 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes, Ugadi is a cherished state holiday on Thursday, March 19, 2026, welcoming the New Year with neem-jaggery concoctions and festive prognostications."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"When does Deepavali occur in Karnataka in 2026?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Deepavali is scheduled for Tuesday, November 10, 2026, enveloping the state in a symphony of lights, confections, and tales of divine triumph."}}]}</script></div><!--/$--></div></div><div class="px-7 sm:px-5 w-[28%] sm:w-full right-articles-section"><!--$--><div class=""></div><!--/$--></div></div></div><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"BreadcrumbList","itemListElement":[{"@type":"ListItem","position":1,"item":{"@id":"/","name":"Home"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":2,"item":{"@id":"/s/personal-finance","name":"Personal Finance"}},{"@type":"ListItem","position":3,"item":{"@id":